result.execSummary:
The defendant Chelsey M. Bass was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of THC, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).
  • Possess Drug Paraphernalia, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Chelsey M. Bass in court with attorney Suzanne Edwards. Prosecuting Atty Jennifer M. Harper appeared for State of Wisconsin.  15CM161 and 16CM10 on the calendar for status today.  Counsel inform the Court that the parties have an agreement for resolution calling for def's plea to THC and paraphernalia charges in 15CM161 for dismissal of 16CM10.  DA states the offer which calls for 2 years probation with conditions to include costs and any required assessments with expungement upon successful completion of probation.  Def pleads no contest to both counts in 15CM161.  Court's colloquy on plea.  Finding of guilty.  SEntence withheld for 2 years probation.  Conditions:  Pay costs; attend, pay for, and successfully complete any treatment or programming required by agent.  Expungement per 973.015 upon successful completion of probation.
